Commentary: FOUR! What a start for Dean Elgar! Tim Southee starts with a length ball, angling it on the pads. Dean Elgar flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary! Dean Elgar and South Africa are underway in style!
Tad fuller, around middle, Dean Elgar presents the full face of the bat and defends it out.
Good-length delivery, swinging away, on the pads. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Length ball, outside off, shaping back in. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
On a length, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it. 4 runs off the first over!
Matt Henry starts with a shorter ball, around middle, Sarel Erwee hops and pushes it towards square leg for a brace. Sarel Erwee opens his account!
Length ball, around middle, at 135.3 clicks. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and defends it out.
Back of a length, outside off, swinging away. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Fraction short, this one nips back in, around off, at 137 clicks. Sarel Erwee lets that go through.
Shorter again, outside off, angling it away. Sarel Erwee offers no shot on that.
Back of a length, around middle, Sarel Erwee blocks it out.
Fuller ball now, wide of off. Dean Elgar leans and lets that go through.
Yorker-length delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar digs it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at 133.2 clicks. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it.
Length delivery, around off. Dean Elgar leans and defends it out.
Fuller now, angling it in on the pads. Dean Elgar taps it towards mid-wicket. Kyle Jamieson there dives to his left and makes a good stop.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar stays in his crease and taps it towards gully.
Matt Henry goes 'round the wicket, serves a shorter ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Another delivery on a back of a length, outside off, at 135.3 clicks. Sarel Erwee lets that go through.
Much fuller now, on the pads. Sarel Erwee uses his wrist and flicks it past square leg for a couple of runs.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and blocks it out.
Length ball, nipping back in, around off. Sarel Erwee leaves it, but gets hit on his thigh pads.
Lenght ball, around middle, Sarel Erwee pushes it towards mid on.
Tim Southee goes 'round the wicket as well, and serves a fuller one, angling it on middle, Dean Elgar taps it towards mid-wicket.

Seems our observation was not correct! This one has moved back in a long way off the pitch. From 'round the wicket, Southee hurls across a length ball outside off. Elgar leaves it on merit but the ball nips back in sharply and goes very closely past the off pole. It kept on moving on its way to the keeper who collects it by stretching to his right.
Length ball, shaping back in, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and defends it out.
Tim Southee goes shorter now, around off, Dean Elgar is hurried up by the extra bounce and mistimes his pull shot to square leg.
Beauty! Length ball, swinging away, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller now, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and drives it past cover for a single.
Good-length delivery, nipping back in, outside off. Dean Elgar leans and taps it towards covers and rotates the strike.
Back of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee looks to defend this, but he gets an inside edge towards fine leg, for a single.
Good-length delivery, angling it in on the pads. Dean Elgar tucks it towards square leg. Single taken!
Back of a length, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and blocks it towards cover.
Tad fuller now, around middle, Sarel Erwee leans and blocks it out.
Back of a length, nipping back in, outside off. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it. Good movement there for Tim Southee!
On a length now, wide of off. Dean Elgar offers no shot to that.
Good-length delivery, angling it in, around off. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
EDGED...but does not carry! Much straighter from Tim Southee now! On a length, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to block this, but gets an outside edge towards first slip, who collects it on a bounce!
Beaten! Tad shorter, outside off, this one comes in a bit late. Dean Elgar presses forward and looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone. End of a probing over from Tim Southee!
Good-length delivery, around middle. Sarel Erwee blocks it out solidly.
Another length ball, around off. Sarel Erwee defends it out.
Leg Bye! Shorter now, down the leg side. Sarel Erwee looks to tuck this away, but the ball deflects off his pads and goes towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken!
On a length, shaping away a tad, outside off. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it.
Matt Henry serves a length ball, from 'round the wicket, nipping back in, outside off. Dean Elgar offers no shot on that.
Good-length delivery, firing it on the pads. Dean Elgar flicks it towards fine leg for a single. He retains the strike!
Length ball, an inswinger, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar taps it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tim Southee serves a shorter delivery now, around off. Dean Elgar picks up the length and pulls it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Much better from Southee now! Length ball, this one shapes in a tad, outside off. Dean Elgar tries to defend this but gets beaten as the ball zips past the outside edge.
On a length, around off. Dean Elgar blocks it out watchfully.
Another length ball, angling it in, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar blocks it towards the leg side.
Length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar leans and blocks it out solidly.
Kyle Jamieson starts off with a fuller ball, angling it away from outside off, at 130.4 clicks. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
An outswinger, on a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee offers no shot on that.
Back of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee taps it towards point off the back foot.
Fraction short, around off. Sarel Erwee presents the full face of his bat and defends it out.
Short again, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee lets that go through to the keeper.
Back of a length, this one comes in a tad, down the leg side, at 133.3 clicks. Sarel Erwee looks to flick but misses.
Southee delivers a length ball on the pads, Elgar nudges it to fine leg and picks up a single.
Southee returns to over the wicket for Sarel Erwee. Serves it full and on the driving length outside off, Sarel has nothing to do with it.

Oohhh...that was not too far away from the leg pole. This is an inswinging fuller delivery, around leg and shaping down, Sarel Erwee fails to flick and Tom Blundell dives full length to his right to collect the ball.
Around off, fuller in length and nipping in, it's defended safely on the leg side. Southee is eyeing those pads.
Pitches it up and outside off, Erwee drives it softly to cover-point.
On a length and around off, Sarel is solidly behind the line in defense.
Shaping away from the left-hander, pitching on middle and leg, Elgar offers no shot.
Very full in length and outside off, at 130.6 kph, Elgar defends it towards covers.
Delivers it on a good length around off at 130.7 kph, some extra bounce, Elgar deals with it well and defends it down towards square leg.

Excellent delivery from Jamieson. Great variation. After bowling a few outswingers, he brings one back in. It though has too much height on it and strikes Elgar high on the pads who has offered no shot.
Goes full and on middle, this time Elgar uses his bat and wrists it towards square leg.
Serves it on a length, around off and shaping away with the seam movement, Elgar covers the line and shoulders arms. Another maiden for Kyle!
Fuller in length and around middle, Sarel Erwee defends it watchfully from the crease. Looking more assured than he was in his debut Test.
In the channel outside off, shaping away, Sarel Erwee allows it through to the keeper.
Southee attempts for an inswinger but it goes down the leg side, Sarel Erwee tries to buy some cheap runs but fails to connect with his attempted flick shot.
Fuller in length and around off, Sarel Erwee drives it down the ground and beats the diving mid on fielder. Collects a couple.
Too full and close to off, Sarel drives it through the line but finds mid off.
Full in length and on off, shaping back in, Sarel Erwee is on the front foot and drives it off the inner half to mid on.
That's a beauty! Kyle Jamieson speeds in from 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball close to off. Elgar stays back to play the line but it nips away to beat his bat.
This one is pitched just ahead of a length around off, Elgar draws forward and pushes it with gentle hands to covers for a quick run.
Very full and on middle, at 129.7 kph, Sarel Erwee brings his bat down in time and keeps it out to mid-wicket.
Serves it on a length around leg, Sarel tries to work it on the leg side but perhaps gets some inside edge onto the pads.

FOUR! Here comes the first boundary for Sarel Erwee. Short in length and outside off, leaving the batter with the angle, Sarel goes on his toes and steers it with a straight bat through point for a boundary. Kyle Jamieson won't mind that shot as he went with a straight bat and there was every chance of an outside edge.
Pitches it up and around off, it's defended watchfully to the off side.

IN THE AIR... Elgar's heart would have been in his mouth. Fuller and outside off, a loose drive from Elgar, away from his body and he chips it past the diving point fielder. Three runs are taken. Elgar knows that was not a great shot.
In the channel outside off, Erwee allows it through to the keeper.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Sarel drives it square of the wicket on the off side for another three runs in this over. Showing more intent which was lacking in the first Test.
Back of a length and outside off, Dean shoulders arms.
Identical to the last delivery, once again Elgar covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Sharp movement. Henry brings a length ball back into the batsman from around off, Elgar has his bat down in time as he keeps it out to square leg.
Darts it in, very full and around off, Sarel Erwee digs it out to the off side.
In the channel outside off, on a good length and angling away, Sarel lets it through to the keeper.
Keeps it full and around off, getting it to seam away from the left-hander, Erwee covers the line and allows it through to the keeper.
That's a risky shot! Jamieson delivers it on a fuller length and forces the batsman to have a go at it. Erwee drives it through covers for a couple of runs.
Digs it in short, around leg, Sarel Erwee stands back and pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Puts it on a fuller length around off, Dean Elgar is on the front foot as he defends it to covers.
On a length and outside off, shaping back in a little, Sarel Erwee has nothing to do with it.
Matt Henry gets a bit closer to the stumps, on a length and again it's moving back in, Sarel Erwee lets it be. Tom Blundell does well to collect it with a dive.
Angling down the leg side, it's tucked behind square leg for a couple of runs.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! That's a good shot! Full in length around middle and leg, Sarel Erwee leans across and flicks it firmly through backward square leg for a boundary.
On middle, turned on the leg side but straight to mid-wicket.
The line is straight from Kyle Jamieson. Elgar tucks it on the leg side but finds the fielder in front of square leg.
Short in length and outside off, Elgar gets across to guard his stumps and then shoulders arms.
Almost drags it on! Fuller in length and outside off, at 127 clicks, Dean Elgar tries to drive away from his body but gets a big inside edge onto the pads.
Around off, on a length and angling in, Elgar covers the line and offers a straight bat in defense.
Angling in from around off, the batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Fullish and outside off, it lands and moves away a shade, Elgar has nothing to offer.
Delivers it on a length around leg, at 139 kph, Erwee stays back to work it on the leg side but misses and gets hit high on the pads.

Well left! Back of a length, around off and shaping in a bit, Sarel Erwee offers no shot. The ball though keeps on swerving to the right of the keeper and Tom Blundell once again makes a great stop behind the stumps.
In the zone outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Streaky! Henry goes short with his length, outside off at 132 kph, Erwee goes on his toes to cut it through the line but it takes the inner edge, beats the stumps and scoots away to the fine leg fence.
Bouncer and on middle, Sarel Erwee ducks.
Short in length on middle, it's pulled in control by Erwee as he sends it to deep square leg for a single.
Full and around off, angling in, Sarel is on the front foot and defends it back with a straight bat.
A gentle outswinger outside off, at 128.5 kph, Sarel Erwee watches it closely before making a leave.
Fractionally short and on off, Erwee goes back and defends it towards cover-point.

FOUR! Glorious! Fuller in length and outside off, at 128.5 kph, Sarel Erwee nicely leans into the drive and thumps it down the ground for a boundary at long off. The 50-run stand comes up and this is the first for the opening wicket for them in 16 innings, informs the on-air commentator.
Around off, on a length, blocked off the front foot.
Uses the angle of the bowler and nudges it behind square leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller ball, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to drive but gets an outside edge towards gully.
On a length now, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Ouch! A shorter ball, around middle, Sarel Erwee looks to tuck this away but he misses and gets hit on the groin area. Sarel Erwee seems to be in some pain here.
Back of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee hops and taps it towards cover for a quick single.
Much fuller now, outside off. Dean Elgar drives, but he gets an inside edge onto his pads. The ball rolls towards covers and the batters cross ends.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Kyle Jamieson serves a shorter ball from 'round the wicket, outside off, at 126.6 clicks. Dean Elgar lets that go through.
Back of a length again, outside off. Dean Elgar offers no shot on that.
Good-length delivery, angling it in on middle. Dean Elgar tucks it towards square leg.
Kyle Jamieson drops it short now, outside off, at 127.7 kph. Dean Elgar stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Extra bounce! A tad shorter, around middle, Dean Elgar does well to get his glove on it and keep it away.
Angling it in, on a good length, around off. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Colin de Grandhomme begins with a fuller ball, nipping back in, on middle. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards mid on.
Full again, an inswinger, around middle. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards mid-wicket. Neil Wagner there dives to his left and does well to stop the ball.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee taps it towards point.
Full now, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards mid off.
FOUR! Glorious! Pitches this one up, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and drives it past cover for a beautiful boundary.
Well bowled! Tad shorter, outside off. Sarel Erwee looks to have a poke at it but gets beaten.
Touch fuller, around middle, Dean Elgar shows the full face of the bat and taps it past mid on for a brace.
Tad shorter now, shaping away, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Back of a length again, outside off. Dean Elgar lets that go through to the keeper.
Neil Wagner drops it short again, down the leg side. Dean Elgar pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Top shot! Perfect placement and exquisite timing on that! Another shorter one, outside off. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and pushes it away from his body past cover for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Very full, on middle. Dean Elgar blocks it out solidly.
Good-length delivery, angling it in on middle. Dean Elgar taps it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Much fuller now, outside off, at 122.1 clicks. Dean Elgar pushes it towards mid off.
Full again, around middle, Dean Elgar tucks it towards mid-wicket. Kyle Jamieson there slides and does well to keep it to only a single.
Back of a length, around the thigh pads. Sarel Erwee flicks it towards fine leg. Tom Blundell runs to his right and cuts it out. Single.
Full, on middle. Dean Elgar pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball, angling it on middle, Sarel Erwee taps it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Neil Wagner drops it short now, around middle. Dean Elgar looks to pull but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, shaping away, around off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out.
On a length again, wide of off, shaping away. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Tad shorter, outside off. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and looks to push this away, but he gets an outside edge past cover-point for a brace.
Neil Wagner drops it short, around middle. Sarel Erwee ducks underneath it.
Good running! On a length, around middle, Dean Elgar leans and taps it to covers and scampers through to the other end.
No ball! Outside off, on a length. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone. Colin de Grandhomme oversteps and a no-ball is given!
Length, outside off. Sarel Erwee defends it out.
On a length again, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards covers.
Tad fuller, around middle, Sarel Erwee tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller now, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans, drives, but finds the fielder at cover.
Another fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee once again drives and finds Tim Southee at covers who does well to stop the ball.
Here we go... Shorter ball, down the leg side. Dean Elgar ducks and lets that go through.
Back of a length again, spraying it down the leg side. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Neil Wagner goes 'round the wicket and serves a short ball, down the leg side once again. Dean Elgar offers no shot.
Fraction short, around middle, Dean Elgar taps it past short leg.
Back of a length, down the leg side. Dean Elgar does not fiddle with it.
Short, down leg, Dean Elgar ducks and leaves it alone. A maiden over for Neil Wagner!
Tad fuller, shaping in, outside off. Sarel Erwee is solid in his front foot defense.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out off the front foot.
Good-length delivery, on the pads. Sarel Erwee works it away towards square leg for a brace.

FOUR! Maiden Test fifty for Sarel Erwee! A fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans forward, looks to drive, but the ball goes off the outer half of the bat past point for a boundary. He raises his bat!
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and defends it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone. That will be Lunch on Day 1!
Fuller ball, angling it in, around middle, Dean Elgar clips it towards square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Much fuller now, around off. Sarel Erwee shows the full face of the bat and pushes it down the ground to long off for three runs.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Back of a length, around middle. Dean Elgar tucks it to square leg.
A bit of a collision while running between the wickets for the batters, but no harm done! A length ball, around middle, Dean Elgar taps it towards mid on for a single.
Around off, on a length and angling in, Elgar defends it off his front foot.
Full and around middle and leg, it's clipped through square leg for two.
Fullish and around off, Elgar pushes it gently in the gap at covers for another couple.
FOUR! Just a push and it has raced away! Full and around off, Elgar offers the full face of the bat and caresses it down through mid on for a boundary.
Around off on a length, defended to the off side.
In the corridor of uncertainty, that is left alone for the keeper to collect.
FOUR! A flurry of runs after Lunch for South Africa. Kyle Jamieson delivers it on a length around leg, Sarel Erwee picks it up off his pads and eases it down to fine leg for a boundary.
Angling away from the batsman, on a length, Sarel punches it to extra cover where Neil Wagner makes a diving stop.
Bowls it on a length and wide outside off, it's an easy leave for Sarel.
Back of a length, outside off, Erwee goes on his toes and taps it down to cover-point.
Lands it on a length around middle and off, shaping away, Sarel Erwee covers the line and shoulders arms.
Short in length around off, Erwee pulls it from the back foot but finds the fielder in front of square on the leg side.
A bit short in length around off, Elgar dabs it down to the left of point for a quick run.
Some movement on this occasion, full and around off, curling in at 124.4 kph, Sarel Erwee defends it from the inner half of his blade.
Serves it on a good length and outside off, Erwee shoulders arms.

FOUR! Shot of authority! Southee pitches it up and around off, at 130.2 kph, Sarel Erwee presses forward and plays a punchy drive down the ground through mid off. 100 comes up - this is the first century stand for the opening wicket for South Africa, away from home, since 2012.
Eases a full ball down towards mid on and crosses for a hesitant single as the fielder makes a diving stop.
Uses the angle of the bowler of the works it through mid-wicket for a run. 25 runs in the 4 overs after Lunch.
The better shoulders arms to let that one through outside off.
Outside off, left alone.
A touch short on off, angling away, Sarel Erwee lifts his bat skywards and allows it through.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it safely to the off side.
Delivers it on a good length outside off, angling away, Sarel lets it through.
Lands it on middle and off, Erwee defends it watchfully to the off side.
A tempter outside off, short and wide, Elgar has nothing to do with it.
Fuller and on off, defended back.
Hurls across a length ball on off, Elgar pushes at it with an angled bat and gets it away off the outer half to gully.
Brilliant delivery, a rare play and a miss in this session. Perhaps the first one. Southee delivers it on a length outside off, getting it to hold its line, Elgar pokes inside the line and misses.
Wide outside off, Elgar has nothing to do with it.
In the zone outside off, Elgar makes a watchful leave. Two maidens on the bounce!
Sliding down the leg side, Sarel eases it off his pads to deep square leg for a single.
Good shot! Fuller in length, around off, Elgar doesn't try to overhit it, just pushes it through mid off for three runs.
Shortish and outside off, left alone by Erwee.
That is left alone for the keeper to collect.
Close leave. This one is delivered close to off, angling away, Sarel knows his off stump and allows it through.
Taps a length ball down to covers and keeps strike with a single.
Drifting down the leg side, Sarel Erwee fails to flick and it goes off the pads to the leg side. A leg bybe.

OUT! BOWLED! What a sight for a fast bowler! Hitting the top of off and Nelson strikes! This is beautiful from Tim Southee. He speeds in from 'round the wicket and delivers it close to off on a good length. The angle takes it into the batter, Elgar tries to defend but is squared up as the ball nips away a shade to beat the outside edge of his bat. It goes on to tickle the top of the off stump and New Zealand have finally managed to get a breakthrough. The century stand is over and Tim Southee has 50 Test wickets at the Hagley Oval.
Howout: b Tim Southee

Commentary: Full and angling in around off, defended off the front foot.
The batter is not interested in playing at that.
Lands it around off, on a length, it's defended.
Movement in the air as it lands on a fuller length around off, Markram covers the line and dead-bats it on the off side. End of a successful over for New Zealand.
Back of a length, around off and seaming away, Sarel Erwee shoulders arms.
Another delivery in the corridor of uncertainty, Erwee lets it be.
On a driving length outside off, Sarel offers no shot.

Well stopped! Fuller in length and outside off, Sarel Erwee plays a full-fledged cover drive but Neil Wagner does well to stop it partially with a dive. They look for a run but then Erwee sends his partner back.
On a length around off, angling away, it's left alone.
Good length and on off, angling away, Sarel Erwee keeps on leaving. He is looking to take no risk at the moment after the fall of Elgar's wicket.
On a length and around off, angling in, Markram defends it from the back foot.
Beauty! Fuller and closer to off, moving away a hint, Markram presses forward to cover the line and shoulders arms.
FOUR! Nice way to open your account! Fuller and outside off Aiden Markram leans into the drive and strokes it elegantly through covers for a boundary.
Darts it in full, around off, it's blocked off the front foot.
Short in length and outside off, Markram punches it from the back foot to mid off where Neil Wagner makes a fine diving stop.
Around middle, on a length, Markram offers a straight blade in defense.
In the channel outside off, on a good length, Sarel Erwee has been excellent with his leaves so far.
Pitches it up and outside off, the invitation is there to drive but Erwee doesn't accept it.
On a length around off, blocked off the back foot to the off side.
Close to off on a length, angling away, Sarel is on the back foot, covering his stumps, as he shoulders arms.
Full and on middle, shaping in a shade, Sarel Erwee tries to defend but it takes the inner half and rolls behind square leg for one.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it towards mid on.

EDGED... and does not carry! Fuller ball, angling it in, outside off. Sarel Erwee looks to drive, but he gets an outside edge which falls just short of the first slip fielder. Good start from Matt Henry!
Tad full, on middle and leg. Sarel Erwee flicks it past mid-wicket for a brace.
Shorter ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and taps it towards point.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! A half-volley, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and drives it beautifully past covers for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Fuller now, around middle. Sarel Erwee pushes it with the inner half of his bat towards mid on.
Tad shorter, hint of away swing, outside off. Sarel Erwee, on back foot, blocks it out.
Another back of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee taps it towards covers off the back foot.
Neil Wagner drops it short again, outside off. Sarel Erwee covers the line and blocks it out solidly.
On a length, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Sarel Erwee defends it out.
This one lands on a length, around middle. Sarel Erwee taps it towards min on. A maiden for Neil Wagner!
Back of a length, outside off. Aiden Markram taps it towards point.

Short again, around middle. Aiden Markram stays in his crease and looks to defend this, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards gully. Henry Nicholls, there fails to grab the ball, and a single is taken!
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out.
Length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
FOUR! Classy! Fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee waits for it, leans into the drive, and creams it past covers for a boundary.
Fuller again, around middle, Sarel Erwee closes the face of his bat and tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Neil Wagner serves a length ball, from over the wicket, around off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out.
Tad full, around middle. Sarel Erwee defends it out.
This one lands full, outside off. Sarel Erwee drives but finds the fielder at mid off.

FOUR! Sarel Erwee is scoring runs freely here! Another top shot! Fuller again, on middle. Sarel Erwee just pushes it uppishly past mid on for a boundary. Neil Wagner has overstepped and a no ball is called as well!
Length ball, on middle, Sarel Erwee tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Touch fuller, outside off. Aiden Markram dabs it towards point.
Length, around middle and leg. Aiden Markram nudges it to mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, n the pads. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Length, on middle, at 137.9 clicks. Aiden Markram blocks it out.
Tad shorter, around off. Aiden Markram looks to defend, but the ball goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid-wicket.
Fuller now, around off. Aiden Markram defends it out.
On a length, around middle and leg. Aiden Markram works it away towards mid on.
This one lands on a length, around off. Aiden Markram stays in his crease and defends it out watchfully.
Touch fuller, outside off. Sarel Erwee gets an inside edge onto his pads as he tries to defend.
Good-length delivery, darting on the pads. Sarel Erwee nudges it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Shorter this time, outside off. Sarel Erwee gets on his toes and blocks it out.
Short again, around middle, Sarel Erwee miscues his pull towards square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram leans and defends it out.
Overpitches this one, around off. Aiden Markram drives but finds the fielder at covers who stops the ball with a dive.
Length, outside off. Sarel Erwee offers no shot on that.
Back of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee will watch it sail through to the keeper.
An inswinger, on a length, around middle, Sarel Erwee taps it towards mid-wicket.
Touch short, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Lovely shot! Overpitches this delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and drives it past cover. The ball will not race away to the boundary, but the batters pick up 3 runs. He moves on to 92!
Length, around off. Aiden Markram defends it out.
Shouts of 'catch it' there! A shorter ball, around middle. Sarel Erwee miscues his pulls towards fine leg, off his gloves, for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Fraction short again, around off. Aiden Markram presents the full face of the bat and defends it out.
Much fuller now, outside off. Aiden Markram drives with the outer half of his bat towards cover-point.
Outside off, on a length. Aiden Markram offers no shot on that!

EDGED...and falls short once again! This is the third time we have seen this! A length ball, outside off. Aiden Markram looks to defend this, but the ball goes off the outside edge, falling just short of the first slip fielder, Daryl Mitchell. He fails to stop it as well and a single is taken!
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram defends it out.
Fuller now, around middle. Aiden Markram blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram pushes this away towards mid off.
Touch shorter, around off. Aiden Markram gets an inside edge onto his pads while trying to defend.
Shorter ball, around middle. Aiden Markram pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller now, a hint of away swing, around off. Aiden Markram defends it out.
Shorter ball, spraying it down the leg side. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Neil Wagner drops it short now, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee ducks under it.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and taps it towards mid-wicket.
Another shorter ball, spraying it down the leg side. Sarel Erwee lets that go through to the keeper.
Short again, around middle. Sarel Erwee ducks and lets it go.
Neil Wagner ends with a short ball again, down the leg side. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Nice shape for Colin de Grandhomme. Lands it full and close to off, shaping away, Aiden makes a watchful leave.
Another outswinger, in the channel outside off, Markram has nothing to do with it.
Back of a length, on top of off, Aiden is on his toes as he defends.
Very full and on middle, Markram pushes it down to mid on.
The batter shoulders arms to let that one through.
Angling in around off, on a length and straightening off the seam, Markram stays on the back foot and defends it down.
Wagner continues with his plan from 'round the wicket. Hurls across a delivery on the shorter side around leg, Sarel tucks it to square leg.
Short and down the leg side, left alone with ease.
Digs it in short again, around middle and leg, Sarel Erwee jumps and taps it down to short leg.
Darts in a short ball around leg, at 132 kph, Erwee fails to glance and it flies past Southee at leg gully for a leg bye.
From over the wicket, a length ball is angled across the batter, Markram pushes it to point.
On a good length around middle, shaping in, Markram goes firmly on the back foot in defense.
Delivers it on a length around off, Sarel Erwee goes on the back foot and defends. He stays on 93.
Lands it on a length and outside off, it's defended off the back foot to covers.
Late movement. Colin de Grandhomme feeds it on a length around middle and leg, Sarel Erwee tries to work it on the leg side but misses and is hit on the back leg.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Full and around off, angling in, Sarel defends it back.
Angles in a length ball on off, Erwee defends it from the back foot. Another maiden, 5 in a row. Just a leg bye during this period.
Pitches it up and outside off, Aiden drives but finds the fielder at covers.
Slightly short and around off, Aiden sticks on the back foot in defense.
On middle and off, at 124.7 kph, Markram wrists it on the leg side but finds mid-wicket. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Fuller in length and on middle, at 128.8 kph, Aiden walks right across the stumps and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single. Had he missed, he was a plumb lbw candidate.

THAT'S A SNORTER! Sarel Erwee takes his eyes off the ball and suffers a blow on his elbow. Neil Wagner bangs it in short, around middle, Erwee is taken by surprise as he attempts to sways away. Fails to do so and is hit on the elbow.
Ticks off from 93 with a single. Short and around leg,it's worked down to fine leg.
FOUR! Good timing! Aiden Markram receives a full ball in his half, around middle and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. 150 comes up!
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Good length and close to off, angling in, Sarel defends it from the back foot.
A gentle delivery, on a length and outside off, angling in, Sarel Erwee allows it through.
Serves another delivery in the channel outside off, testing the patience of a batsman on 94, Erwee allows it through once more.
Fuller and off, defended to the off side.
Moves to 96! Angling into the left-hander, Sarel Erwee uses the angle to his advantage and tucks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Delivers it on a length and outside off, angling away, Markram allows it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Lovely shot! A touch short and around leg, Aiden Markram goes on the back foot and glances it through square leg for a lovely boundary.
Bowls it on a length and outside off, it's left alone.
Good length, on off, defended off the back foot to the off side.
Pitches it up and around off, angling away again, Aiden Markram drives it square of the wicket on the off side. Finds point.

Switches to 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball around off, Markram uses the crease and turns it in the gap at mid-wicket. He takes a single, turns for the second run but it's not available.
Full and wide outside off, swinging in the air, Markram drives it off his front foot to covers.
Puts it on a fuller length around off, angling in and straightening, Markram defends it near his front pad.
Bowls an outswinger, on a length and outside off, Aiden shoulders arms.
Good leave. This time Colin de Grandhomme delivers it on a length and just outside off, it holds its line and Markram shoulders arms.
Darts it in full, around off, Aiden defends it off his front foot.
Full and angling in around off, Aiden is forward in defense.
Bouncer around leg, Sarel ducks.
Short again, down the leg side, Sarel shoulders arms.

FOUR! HUNDRED FOR ERWEE! His first in Tests and it's been a terrific knock! Short in length, around middle and nicely sitting up for the batter, Sarel rides the bounce and pulls it in the gap at square leg for a boundary. It's been a responsible and highly skilful knock. Very challenging at the start but he weathered the storm and now has a century to his name. The helmet comes off and he raises his arms in celebration. Your first hundred will always have a special place in your heart. Meanwhile, the 50-run stand has also come up.
Too full in length, around off, Sarel defends it to the off side.
Sliding down the leg side, Sarel lets it be.
On a good length around middle, Sarel Erwee defends it solidly to end the over and this session. Tea on Day 1!
Starts a new spell by angling in a length ball around off, Aiden Markram defends it from the crease.
Serves it short and outside off, Markram rocks back to cut but finds the point fielder.
Full and angling in around off, shaping away a shade, Markram covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Tim goes wide of the crease and angles in a full ball around off, Markram drives it back to the bowler.
Around middle and off, on a length, Aiden defends it off his back foot.
Pitches it up and around off, an outswinger, Markram presses forward and defends it under his watchful eyes.
Hurls across a length ball, around off and angling away, Sarel Erwee has taken a fresh guard, wants to play a big knock, and watchfully leaves it to start with!
Back of a length, around middle and off, Sarel Erwee gets behind the line and defends it to short mid-wicket.
Sprays a full ball wide outside off, Sarel has an easy leave to make.

In the line of the stumps at 134 kph, Sarel gets behind the line again and defends it towards mid-wicket. The fielder picks it up and has a wayward shy at the striker's end. It goes behind the keeper and they cross.
Shortish and on off, Markram goes on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
In the channel outside off, a pretty harmless delivery on a length, Aiden has nothing to do with it.
Touch fuller, angling it in, around off. Sarel Erwee gets an outside edge towards gully but it falls away from the fielder.
Leg bye! On a length, darting it on the pads. Sarel Erwee looks to flick but misses. The ball deflects off the pads and rolls towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken!
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram defends it out.
Fuller now, around middle. Aiden Markram closes the face of his bat and tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Swing and a miss! Full in length, wide of off. Sarel Erwee leans and looks to drive but gets beaten.
Touch fuller again, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Very full, around middle, Aiden Markram shows the full face of his bat and drives it past mid on for a glorious boundary.
Another fuller ball, around middle. Aiden Markram presses forward and blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, around off. Aiden Markram defends it out off the back foot.
Another full-length delivery, around middle. Aiden Markram flicks it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Fraction short, around middle, Aiden Markram shuffles across and taps it towards square leg.
FOUR! Top shot! Another short ball, around middle, Aiden Markram picks up the length and pulls it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Tim Southee drops it short now, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee ducks underneath it.
Fuller this time, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
On a length, around middle. Sarel Erwee blocks it out.
Beauty! Good-length delivery, outside off, nipping away a tad. Sarel Erwee looks to defend this one but gets beaten as the ball zips past through the outside edge.
Another length ball, around the fourth stump line. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Length ball, around off. Sarel Erwee defends it out off the back foot.
Length ball, outside off. Aiden Markram lets that go through.
FOUR! Aiden Markram is looking better with every shot! Full, around middle. Aiden Markram drives it past mid on for a boundary.
Another full ball, around middle, Aiden Markram pushes it towards mid on.
This one lands on a length, around middle. Aiden Markram defends it out.
Wide called for height! Too short on this occasion, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone and wide is called!
Full in length, around middle and leg. Aiden Markram clips it towards square leg for a single.
Full again, outside off. Sarel Erwee drives it to covers.
Length ball, around middle. Aiden Markram taps it towards mid-wicket.
Angling it in, around leg, on a length. Aiden Markram flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, shaping in, around the pads. Sarel Erwee works it away towards deep square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Shaping away, outside off, on a length. Aiden Markram lets that go through to the keeper.
Fuller this time, around off. Aiden Markram blocks it out.
Full in length, around off. Sarel Erwee pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! WOW! That's a treat to watch! Kyle Jamieson overpitches this one, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and drives it past cover for a boundary.
Very full again, outside off. Sarel Erwee drives it towards cover.
Kyle Jamieson maintains the same length. Full and outside off. Sarel Erwee leans to drive, but misses!
Outside off, on a length. Sarel Erwee defends it off the back foot.
Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
An outswinger, on a length, outside off. Aiden Markram lets that go through.
Touch fuller, around middle, Aiden Markram defends it out.
Length delivery, around off. Aiden Markram looks to defend but gets an outside edge towards gully, who collects the ball on a couple of bounces.
FOUR! Top shot! Matt Henry drops it short, around middle and leg. Aiden Markram picks up the length and pulls it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Aiden Markram blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Shorter ball now, around middle, Sarel Erwee pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Aiden Markram is putting everything away now! A fuller ball, angling in on the pads. Aiden Markram uses his wrists and flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, outside off, shaping away. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Another length ball, around middle. Aiden Markram defends it out.
Edged...and this one falls short again! Tad fuller, outside off. Aiden Markram gets forward to drive but gets an outside edge which falls short of the fielder at second slip.
Length ball, outside off. Aiden Markram lets that go through.
Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Much fuller now, outside off. Sarel Erwee drives but finds the fielder at cover.
Back of a length, around off. Sarel Erwee defends it out off the back foot.
Full in length, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards cover.
Tad fuller, outside off. Sarel Erwee opens the face of the bat and pushes it past point for a single.
Matt Henry drops it short, on middle. Aiden Markram pulls with the inner half of his bat towards deep mid-wicket. Three taken!
Length, outside off. Aiden Markram shoulders his arms at it.
Fraction short, outside off. Aiden Markram presents the full face of his bat and defends it out.
Back of a length, around the thigh pad. Aiden Markram tucks it to square leg.
Shaping away, on a length, wide of off. Aiden Markram offers no shot on that.
Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Aiden Markram shuffles across and defends it out.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Finally, an edge carries to slip! Neil Wagner has broken this partnership and Aiden Markram who was looking so good has to depart. Very full this time, outside off, forcing the batter to drive. Aiden Markram does exactly that, he leans to drive, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip. Daryl Mitchell there pouches it safely. South Africa lose their second wicket after an 88-run stand!
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Fuller in length and outside off, Sarel drives it off his front foot to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! One brings two and New Zealand are making a comeback late in the evening. Matt Henry hurls across a length ball, outside off and angling away, Sarel Erwee tries driving away from his body but all he manages is a thick outside edge. A simple catch for Tom Blundell and that ends a fantastic knock. The hosts are roaring now and have two new batters at the crease. The second new ball is also not far away.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary: Around off, on a length, defended off the back foot.

FOUR! Streaky! That's a snorter from Matt Henry. This one shoots up from a shortish length around off, Temba Bavuma is taken by surprise. He hops, tries to fend it away and edges it in the process. It goes over the slip cordon for a boundary. 200 South Africa!

FOUR! Again it's unintentional. Matt Henry delivers it on a length and close to off, Bavuma tries to leave but is late in taking his bat away. It kisses the bottom edge and runs through the gap at the slip cordon for a boundary.
On a length around off, pushed in the gap at covers for a single. End of another successful over for the Kiwis.
Angling away from the batsman, outside off, Bavuma leaves.
On a length and around off, defended off the back foot.
Outside off, Bavuma lets it be.
The batter shoulders arms to let that one through.
Fullish and outside off, Temba drives it towards mid off and races across to the other end.
Delivers it in the zone outside off, Rassie has nothing to do with it.
Keeps it on a length and close to off, Bavuma sticks on the back foot and defends.
Hurls across a length delivery in the channel outside off, Temba offers no shot.
Beaten! Brings a length ball in with the angle and then takes it away with the seam movement, Bavuma pushes at it and misses.
Around off, on a length, blocked.
Fuller and on off, driven back to the bowler.
Outside off, Bavuma has an easy leave this time.
Bowls it in the region outside off, landing around off and angling away, Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Fuller and closer to off, Rassie is forward as he blocks it near his front pad.
Fuller and outside off, this time Rassie drives through the line but finds the fielder at covers.
On a good length this time, shaping away outside off, van der Dussen shoulders arms.
Wagner continues to probe around the off-stump channel. He takes it away with the angle, Rassie presses forward to cover the line and then makes a leave.
Pitches it up and close to off, Rassie defends it from the lower half of his bat.

Uppish but no short leg in place. Jamieson serves it on a length around off, getting it to shape back in, Temba draws forward in defense but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It lobs towards the vacant short leg region and then dies down.
FOUR! Fine shot! Back of a length, around off, Temba Bavuma stands tall, uses every inch of his height to get on top of the bounce and punches it in front of square on the off side for a boundary.
This one is served wide outside off, Bavuma has nothing to do with it.
Soft outside edge! Kyle Jamieson lands it close to off, on a length and it straightens, Bavuma pushes inside the line with gentle hands and edges it towards the slip cordon. Doesn't carry.
Short and wide outside off, Bavuma chases it and cuts it from the bottom part of his bat. It dribbles through point for a couple of runs.

FOUR! Bavuma has raced away to 20 in no time! Short in length, around off, once again Temba rocks back and punches it sweetly through covers. The outfield is lightning quick and it's a boundary. 10 from the over!
Angling away from the batsman, outside off, an easy leave for Rassie.
On a length and close to off, van der Dussen stays on the back foot and pushes it to covers.
Shot! A juicy half-volley, outside off, Rassie leans forward and drives it wide of mid off for three runs. He opens his account.
Delivers it on a good length, outside off, Temba covers the line and shoulders arms.
Fullish and around off, Bavuma stays back and pushes it away with an angled bat to point.
Too wide outside off, on a good length, a comfortable leave for Temba.
Serves it on a shortish length outside off, Rassie stays back to guard his stumps as he makes a leave.
Identical to the last delivery, unlike Bavuma, Rassie is not chasing those outside off.
Fuller and straighter this time, at 131.6 kph, Rassie van der Dussen flicks it towards mid-wicket where the fielder makes a diving stop. Cannot prevent the single though.
On a length around off, Bavuma stays inside the crease and defends.
Misses out this time, Bavuma. Short in length, wide outside off, Temba cracks it off his back foot but finds Colin de Grandhomme at covers.
This is better, full and around off, Temba gets on the front foot and defends it solidly.
Beaten! Very good area from Wagner. He puts it on a fuller length around off and gets it to nip away, Rassie tries defending off the front foot but misses.
Peach! Even fuller this time, outside off and enticing the drive from the batter, Rassie van der Dussen goes after it, flat-footed and gets beaten by the away movement.
Delivers it on a good length, outside off, Rassie drops his wrists and allows it through to the keeper.
Full in length and close to off, Rassie chooses to remain on the back foot as he blocks it to the off side.
Angling away, on a length and around off, Rassie van der Dussen defends it with an angled bat to gully.
Fuller and outside off, once again Rassie pushes at it with an angled bat and places it towards point. A probing over by Wagner!
Serves it on a length and outside off, Bavuma allows it through to the keeper.
Jamieson goes wide of the crease and feeds it on a length around off. It lands and straightens as Bavuma shoulders arms.
Another length delivery in the channel outside off, Bavuma stays back and allows it through.
Fuller and closer to off, Bavuma pushes it towards gully where Henry Nicholls makes the stop.
Back of a length, outside off and shaping away, Temba shoulders arms.
Fractionally short and around off, targeting the stumps, Temba gets behind the line and blocks.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length around off, Rassie goes on the back foot and eases it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Fuller and around off, it's jammed out to covers.
Pitches it up and around off, Rassie van der Dussen is drawn forward in defense.
Bouncer around middle and leg, Rassie van der Dussen ducks underneath it.
Wagner oversteps and delivers a full ball down the leg side, Rassie fails to flick and it goes off his pads to fine leg. They take a couple of leg byes.
In the channel outside off, on a length and angling away, van der Dussen allows it through to close the over.
On a length, shaping away, outside off, at 128.7 clicks. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Touch fuller now, outside off, shaping away, at 124.4 clicks. Temba Bavuma offers no shot.
An outswinger, on a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma lets that go through.
Tad fuller, outside off. Temba Bavuma taps it towards cover.
Length ball, swinging away, around off. Temba Bavuma pushes it past mid off for a couple of runs.
Another length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma does not fiddle with it.
On a length, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen is taken by surprise due to the extra bounce, but he does well to get some bat on it as he blocks.

JAFFA! What a peach of a delivery! On a length, nipping back in, around middle, Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend this but gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball flies just over the stumps and goes towards the keeper. He got bowled in a similar fashion in the first Test.

An appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no! A length ball, angling in, on the pads. Rassie van der Dussen goes for the flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. The replay shows it would have missed the wickets and it's a good call from Tom Latham to not take the DRS.
Another length ball, angling in on the pads. Rassie van der Dussen misses his flick and gets pinged on the pads again. A muted appeal only from the bowler.
On a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Lovely delivery! A length ball, shaping away, around the fourth stump line. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone. Well left!

APPEAL FOR AN LBW! Not given. Full in length and around off, nipping back in sharply with extra bounce, Bavuma tries to defend off the front foot but misses. He is pinged on the pads, they appeal but the finger stays down. Southee is pretty confident that he has trapped Bavuma in front. Tom Latham gets convinced and he takes the referral. The Ball Tracking shows that it's heading over the stumps. One review is wasted.
Good-length delivery, moving away, around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
An outswinger, on a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma lets that go through.
This one lands around off and jags back in, on a length. Temba Bavuma defends it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out off the back foot.
On a length now, around off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it out.
Much fuller now, around middle, Rassie van der Dussen pushes it to the fielder at mid on.

A stifled appeal for LBW, but the umpire is unmoved! A length ball, nipping back in from middle and leg, Rassie van der Dussen goes for the flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. That was sliding down leg. Another good decision from the umpire!
Leg bye! Length ball, on the pads. Rassie van der Dussen tries to work this away on the leg side, but he misses and the ball hits his pads and rolls towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken!
Shorter ball, down the leg side. Temba Bavuma misses his flick.
Fuller, shaping away, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
An outswinger, full again, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards mid on.
Southee goes wide of the crease but gets his line all wrong. Full and on the pads, it's tickled down to fine leg for a single.
On a length, around middle, Bavuma works it off his pads to mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, darting on the pads. Temba Bavuma taps it towards mid on.
Pitches this one up, outside off. Temba Bavuma leans and looks to drive, but the ball goes off the inside edge towards mid on.
Matt Henry drops it short, on middle, Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out off the back foot.
On a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend this, the ball goes off the soft outside edge towards gully. Henry Nicholls there dives to his left and makes a good stop.

DROPPED! Oh, dear! A chance goes down! A fuller ball, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen flicks it uppishly towards mid-wicket. Will Young is perfectly stationed there, lifts his hands near his face to take the catch, but fails to grab it. It bursts through his fingers and goes in the deep. They take a couple of runs.
Delivers it on a length around off, Rassie defends it watchfully from the back foot.
Spears it full and around middle, van der Dussen gets behind the line and defends it towards mid on.
Full and angling down the leg side, nudged away behind square leg for a single.
Fuller and on the pads again, it's worked fine to fine leg for two.
On a good length and outside off, Rassie shoulders arms.
Length ball, on the pads. Rassie van der Dussen works it away towards square leg for a single.
Touch fuller, around middle and off. Temba Bavuma looks to drive this but gets an inside edge towards square leg.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Temba Bavuma shows the full face of the bat and defends it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma cuts it towards point where the fielder makes a fine stop.
Length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it towards covers.
Good-length delivery, coming back in, around middle, Rassie van der Dussen clips it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller now, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards mid on.
Shorter ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen punches it to the fielder at mid off.
Pitches it up, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen taps it towards mid on.
Length ball, around off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, around middle, Temba Bavuma pushes it towards mid-wicket. He leaves his crease for a single but decides against it in the end.
Length ball, angling in, around off. Temba Bavuma leans to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On a good length, around middle and swinging in. Temba Bavuma once again gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Touch short, shaping away, around off.  Temba Bavuma taps it towards point.
Fuller now, outside off. Temba Bavuma offers no shot to that.
Length ball, shaping away, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Serves it full and close to off, Rassie closes the face of his bat and works it to square leg.
Lands it on a length and around off, Rassie van der Dussen gets across the stumps a bit and defends it near his body.
In the channel outside off, Rassie offers no shot.

NOT OUT! Fuller and around off, Rassie van der Dussen gets on the front foot and scuffs his drive off the inner half to mid on. He steps out for a run but Bavuma has turned his back on him. The fielder there dives and parries it to mid off who fires a direct hit at the striker's end. New Zealand appeal, it's referred upstairs but the replays find that Rassie is easily home.
Delivers it on a length, around off and shooting off the surface, Rassie van der Dussen tries to defend but gets hit on the splice.
Full in length around middle, angling in, Rassie flicks it off his pads to mid-wicket. That will be it - Stumps on Day 1!
Tim Southee begins with a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Touch fuller, swinging away from around off. Temba Bavuma leans and blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, wide of off. Temba Bavuma offers no shot.
An outswinger, on a length, outside off, at 125.7 clicks. Temba Bavuma lets that go through.
PLAY AND A MISS! Tad shorter now, wide of off. Temba Bavuma stays in his crease and looks to cut this away but misses.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma does not fiddle with it. A maiden to begin with!
Matt Henry starts off with a fuller ball, around middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen flicks it past mid-wicket for three runs. First runs of the day!
Tad shorter, outside off, shaping away. Temba Bavuma looks to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma knocks it in front of the cover fielder.
Back of a length, around middle. Temba Bavuma defends it out off the back foot.
Outside off, shorter in length, shaping in. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Fuller now, around middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen works it away towards square leg for a brace.
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Pitches it up, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leans and drives it past cover. Kyle Jamieson chases the ball, puts in a dive and keeps the ball away from the rope. Three taken!
On a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma defends it out watchfully.
Beaten! Another length ball, shaping away from around off. Temba Bavuma leans and looks to defend this away from his body, but gets beaten.
This one lands on a length, angling it in, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Tad shorter, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen punches it towards cover.
Outside off, shaping away, on a length. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.

DROPPED! The first chance of the morning goes down! Tim Southee, the culprit! A fuller ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leans and looks to drive, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards third slip. Tim Southee there goes low for the catch but spills it out.

Another half-chance! Fuller again, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it uppishly towards the left of the bowler. Matt Henry dives in his follow-through but it drops ahead of his left hand and speeds behind. Colin de Grandhomme gives the chase and then slips while attempting to pick up the ball. Three runs are taken. The 50-run stand comes up!
Extra bounce from a good length around off, Temba Bavuma goes on the back foot and fends it off awkwardly.
Short and around off, this time Temba stands tall and punches it through covers for three runs. End of yet another unfortunate over for Henry, a dropped catch in it.
On a length, around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it within the crease.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Another length ball, outside off, shaping away. Temba Bavuma lets that go through.
Much fuller now, coming in, around off. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards mid off.
FOUR! First boundary of Day 2! Shorter ball, around middle, Temba Bavuma pulls this past square leg for a boundary.
Touch shorter again, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out.

Beaten! A beauty! On a length again, outside off, just nipping away. Rassie van der Dussen stays in his crease and looks to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge. Daryl Mitchell appeals for a catch from first slip but he is the only one doing so.
Good-length delivery, around middle, Rassie van der Dussen looks to flick this on the leg side, but gets a leading edge away from the bowler.
Length, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen works it towards mid-wicket.
Shaping away, outside off, on a length. Rassie van der Dussen taps it towards covers.
Delivers it on a length, close to off, Rassie van der Dussen works it from the inner half of his bat to long leg for a single. Another probing over by Henry.
Length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.

An appeal for LBW, but turned down! A length ball, nipping back in around off. Rassie van der Dussen shuffles across and tries to flick this but misses and gets hit on the pads. The impact is easily outside off.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Tad fuller, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it out off the front foot.
Fuller again, around middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards mid on.
Fuller in length and around off, Rassie gets forward and pushes it to covers where Colin de Grandhomme makes a diving stop.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! This is just what New Zealand wanted! Matt Henry decides to do it all by himself with the catches going down off his bowling. A terrific change in length from him. Hurls across a fantastic yorker, at 132.6 kph, it's going dead straight with the angle, no swing whatsoever on it. Temba Bavuma is a shade early into his shot as the ball dips in front of his bat. It sneaks past the bottom edge and disturbs the off pole. Bavuma's stay is over and New Zealand have their first breakthrough on Day 2.
Howout: b Matt Henry

Commentary: Length ball, angling it in, around middle, Kyle Verreynne defends it out.
Peach! What a delivery! That deserved a wicket! A length ball, shaping away a tad. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge. The ball flies just over the stumps.
Length ball, around middle. Kyle Verreynne flicks it towards mid-wicket.

Quick single! A length ball, darting on the pads. Kyle Verreynne works it away towards square leg and scampers through to the other end. Will Young dives to his right and collects the ball. He has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. Kyle Verreynne dives to make his ground, and he seems to have hurt himself in that process.
On a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out. End of a successful over by Matt Henry!
Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
Good shot! Fuller now, jagging back in around middle, Kyle Verreynne flicks it past mid-wicket. Three taken!
Back of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders his arms at it.
Tad shorter, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.

An appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no! Fuller ball, nipping back in around middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen looks to flick, but misses and gtes hit on his pads. That was definitely sliding down leg.
Length ball, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen closes the face of his bat and tucks it towards square leg.
Beaten! Tad fuller, outside off, shaping away. Kyle Verreynne looks to drive this away from his body and gets beaten!
Length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne defends it out.
Another appeal for LBW, but the umpire turns it down! Another length ball, nipping back in, around middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne looks to flick but misses. That was probably sliding down leg too.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Matt Henry has his second wicket of the morning and is impressing one and all once again. He delivers it on a length outside off, at 133.5 kph, getting it to nip away after landing. Kyle Verreynne, who looked uncomfortable throughout his stay, lunges forward to defend with his bat hanging away from the body. He doesn't account for the movement and ends up edging it to Tom Latham at second slip. He makes no mistake and it's turning out to be a fabulous morning for the home side.
Howout: c Tom Latham b Matt Henry

Commentary: Length ball, around middle, Wiaan Mulder blocks it out solidly.
A beauty to end the over! On a length again, outside off. Wiaan Mulder stays in his crease and looks to defend but misses. Another successful over by Matt Henry, a wicket maiden!
Starts with a full delivery, around off, Rassie defends it on the leg side.
On a length and close to off, Rassie van der Dussen defends it from the back foot.
Beaten! Fuller in length and closer to off, Rassie van der Dussen tries to defend the line but gets beaten by the away movement.
This one is quite wide outside off, shaping away, Rassie has an easy leave this time.
In the channel outside off, quite wide again to bother the batsman who allows it through.
Full and wide outside off, another leave from Rassie van der Dussen to round off the over. A maiden!
Well bowled! Matt Henry keeps his line close to off, shaping away, Mulder feels for it and is beaten.
This one nips back in from a length outside off, Mulder decides to make a leave this time.
Around off, on a length, Wiaan gets opened up in his stance as he defends it to the off side.
Fuller and around off, shaping in, Mulder presses forward confidently and defends it right under his eyes. Solid.
Fuller again, around off, Mulder defends it to the off side
Serves it on a length around off, straightening a hint off the seam Wiaan goes on the back foot and defends it from the outer half of his blade. Third maiden in a row!
Movement there for Jamieson but his line is wide outside off, Rassie van der Dussen has an easy leave.
This one is on a length and outside off, angling in, Rassie van der Dussen stays inside the crease to cover the line and shoulders arms.
On a driving length outside off, Rassie is very watchful at the moment. He just watches the line and allows it through.
Fraction short in length and wide outside off, Rassie van der Dussen lets it be.
Fuller and just outside off, Rassie van der Dussen takes his front leg forward, has a close look at it and then shoulders arms.

Miscommunication but no harm is done. Kyle Jamieson delivers a length ball on middle and leg, Rassie nudges it down to fine leg and takes a single. He wants the second run too and rushes for it. His partner though realizes late and then sets off. The throw comes to the wrong end, i.e. the keeper's end and that allows Wiaan time to race towards the other end.
Fullish and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Plenty of 3s this morning. Full and around off, angling in, Mulder clips it through mid-wicket for three runs.
Lands it on a length, close to off, Rassie van der Dussen defends it from the upper half of his bat. He is looking very tentative against Henry.
Around off, on a length, defended to the off side.
Fuller in length and outside off, could have been left out, but Rassie is very nervous, he gets forward and pushes it to covers.
Taps a length ball to covers and scampers across to the other end.
Bowls it on a length and around off, Rassie defends it from the back foot to the leg side.
Stays on the back foot to a delivery around middle and works it with the angle to square leg. Not in the gap though.

FOUR! Finds the fence! This time it's too full and too straight from Kyle Jamieson, Rassie van der Dussen leans across and flicks it wide of the square leg fielder. It races through and has enough legs to touch the boundary line.
Angling in from a fuller length around off, van der Dussen defends it towards mid on.
On a length, around off and angling in, Rassie defends it from the crease to mid-wicket.
Kyle Jamieson goes wide of the crease and delivers it on a good length outside off. The ball lands and holds its line as Rassie shoulders arms.

My word, that's an interesting shot selection from Mulder. A delivery around middle and leg, angling down, Wiaan Mulder walks forward and across the stumps, exposing two stumps and attempting to flick but misses.
An outswinger in the channel outside off, Wiaan allows it through to the keeper.
Fullish and on off, Wiaan gently works it across the line to mid-wicket.
This one is on a length and around off, shaping away, Mulder shoulders arms.
In the corridor of uncertainty, that is left alone for the keeper to collect.
Fuller in length and on off, angling in, Wiaan Mulder gets forward to cover the line and blocks it safely.

Risky single! Fuller and on off, angling in, Rassie pushes it in front of Wagner at mid-wicket and scampers across to the other end. Neil has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Probably, a better opportunity was at the bowler's end.
On a length and outside off, left alone.
Action replay of the previous delivery. Wiaan has looked a lot assured at the crease.
Fuller and on off, darting in, Mulder defends it solidly to the off side.
An attempted inswinger but the line starts from way wide outside off. Wiaan Mulder has nothing to do with it.
Extra bounce. Back of a length and around off, Wiaan Mulder initially looks to commit himself into the shot but then withdraws his bat.
In the region outside off, van der Dussen allows it through to the keeper.
Full and around leg, it's worked off the pads to deep square leg for a single.
Southee serves it full and just outside off, nipping away, Mulder covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Southee tries to repeat the last delivery from middle and leg. But it lands and skid on with the angle. Mulder helps it off his pads to square leg.
On a length and around off, shaping away, Wiaan Mulder hangs back and decides to play at it at the last moment. He brings his bat down and guides it past gully for a couple of runs.
Around off, on a length, Wiaan stays on the back foot and blocks it safely.
A gentle loosener from Neil Wagner. Serves it a touch short and wide outside off, Rassie allows it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, on top of off, Rassie van der Dussen goes on his toes and plays it down to cover-point.
Around off, on a length and angling away, Rassie plays at it gently and pushes it to point.
Full and way wide outside off, left alone.
Better delivery. Full and around off, shaping back into middle and off, Rassie van der Dussen hops on the back foot and defends it to the leg side.
Delivers it on a length around middle, it's defended from the back foot to the leg side. Maiden.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Wiaan gets across and then shoulders arms.
Digs it in short on middle, Mulder stands back and pulls it behind square leg for a single.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Rassie stays on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Fuller and closer to off, moving back in, Rassie gets behind the line, covers the movement and pushes it towards mid on.
Around middle and off, angling in, Rassie van der Dussen works it on the leg side and finds the fielder standing in front of square on the leg side.
On a length and around middle, Rassie stays back and wrists it behind square leg for a run.
On a length, shaping away, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
This one comes back in a tad, on middle and on a length. Rassie van der Dussen defends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, dear! A wicket in an unusual manner! Neil Wagner cannot believe it himself and has a sheepish smile on his face! But New Zealand will take that! A yorker-length delivery, wide of off at 126.3 kph. Rassie van der Dussen reaches out and tries to squeeze it away but the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip. Daryl Mitchell there pouches it safely. The umpires want to check it for the bump ball but the replays show that it has clearly gone off the outside edge to the fielder. Rassie van der Dussen runs out of his luck eventually - was dropped on 7 and 21.
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Neil Wagner drops it short now, around middle. Marco Jansen ducks underneath it.
Beaten! Outside off, on a length. Marco Jansen looks to defend but gets beaten.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away, at 130.4 clicks. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Length, on middle. Wiaan Mulder blocks it out solidly.
Tad fuller now, around off, shaping in a bit. Wiaan Mulder leans and defends it out.
Angling in, around middle and leg, on a length. Wiaan Mulder taps it towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Beautiful shot! Full again, around middle, Wiaan Mulder presents the full face of the bat and drives it past mid on for a boundary. South Africa need more of these! Just the third boundary of the day.
Length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
Angling in, around middle and on a length. Wiaan Mulder pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball, outside off. Marco Jansen leans and drives it past cover. Three taken!
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Wiaan Mulder looks to defend this but misses.
An appeal for LBW, but turned down! On a length, darting it on the pads. Wiaan Mulder looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad. That was pitching outside leg.
Length, around off. Wiaan Mulder defends it out.
Fuller now, around off. Wiaan Mulder presses forward and blocks it out.
Shaping away, outside off, on a length. Wiaan Mulder shoulders his arms at it.
Good start! Touch shorter, outside off, this one nips away after landing. Marco Jansen looks to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Easy pickings! On a length, darting it on the pads. Marco Jansen flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Length, around off. Marco Jansen stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Touch fuller, on middle. Marco Jansen leans and blocks it out solidly.
This one lands on a length, outside off. Marco Jansen offers no shot.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Second boundary of the over! Kyle Jamieson pitches this one up, around off. Marco Jansen leans and pushes it past mid off for a boundary.
Tad fuller, outside off. Wiaan Mulder leans and blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder lets that go through.
FOUR! Wow, wonderful shot! Tad shorter now, outside off. Wiaan Mulder stays in his crease, gets on his toes and punches it through the gap at covers for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A good comeback by Neil Wagner! He strikes and gets rid of Wiaan Mulder, who was looking assured at the crease. Short in length on middle, Wiaan Mulder stays in his crease and looks to pull this but he is way too early into his shot as the ball arrives late. It flies high towards the keeper off the top edge and Tom Blundell immediately calls for it. He grabs the skier safely and New Zealand lose their seventh wicket.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Fuller, down the leg side. Kagiso Rabada leaves it alone.
On a length, around middle. Kagiso Rabada pushes it back to the bowler.
Length, around middle. Marco Jansen defends it out solidly.
Outside off, on a length. Marco Jansen dabs it towards point.
Back of a length, outside off. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, around middle, Marco Jansen knocks it towards mid on.
Edged and just short of the second slip fielder! A fuller ball, outside off. Marco Jansen leans and looks to defend, but gets an outside edge, towards second slip, who collects it on the bounce.
Length ball, around middle. Marco Jansen blocks it out.
Angling in, around middle and leg, on a length. Kagiso Rabada taps it towards mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Kagiso Rabada stays in his crease and looks to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tad fuller, around off. Kagiso Rabada pushes it towards mid off.
Neil Wagner drops it short now, around middle. Kagiso Rabada ducks under it.
Much fuller, outside off. Kagiso Rabada leans and pushes it past mid off for a couple of runs.
Length, outside off. Kagiso Rabada stays back and looks to block this, but the ball goes off the outside edge and falls short of the fielder at gully. That will be Lunch on Day 2!
Fuller ball, outside off. Marco Jansen drives it towards mid off.
Beauty! On a length, around off, shaping away just a tad. Marco Jansen looks to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, around middle. Marco Jansen dabs it out towards cover.
Fuller now, outside off. Marco Jansen leans and defends it out.
Another full ball, around the off pole. Marco Jansen blocks it out once again.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Angling in, outside off, on a length. Kagiso Rabada gets beaten as he tries to defend this one.
Tad shorter, around off. Kagiso Rabada just taps it towards point. He was in two minds whether to play it or not.
Outside off, on a length. Kagiso Rabada misses as he tries to defend this one.
Shorter ball, outside off. Kagiso Rabada blocks it out.
EDGED AND FOUR! On a length, outside off. Kagiso Rabada leans to drive but gets a thick outside edge past the second slip fielder for a boundary. 300 up!

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! A superb catch by Daryl Mitchell! Neil Wagner gets his man this time and is one away from a 5-wicket haul! He delivers it on a length, around off, shaping away. Kagiso Rabada leans to block this but gets an outside edge between the keeper and first slip. Tom Blundell lets the ball go but Daryl Mitchell is alert and takes a fine catch diving to his right. To be honest, it was Blundell's catch and credit should go to Mitchell for anticipating it so well. South Africa continue to slip.
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Fuller ball, around middle, Marco Jansen blocks it out.
Angling in, around middle, on a length. Marco Jansen pushes it through mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, around off. Keshav Maharaj defends it out.
Fuller now, angling in, around middle and off. Keshav Maharaj looks to defend but gets an inside edge on the leg side.
Outside off, on a length. Keshav Maharaj defends it out.
Length ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj dabs it towards point.
Lands it full and around off, Jansen gets forward and defends it back.
Fuller again, around off, Marco Jansen drives it off his front foot to mid off.
Short and around off, Marco Jansen brings his big frame down as he ducks.
Beaten this time! Some extra bounce for Wagner. He delivers it short again, around off and angling away, Jansen stays back to punch but misses.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Good stop! Angling away from the batter, on a length, Marco Jansen opens the face of his bat and pushes it towards gully where Henry Nicholls makes a fine diving stop.
Delivers it on a length and outside off, Maharaj defends it off his back foot to cover-point.
Almost edges it behind. Matt Henry lands it on a good length outside off, shaping away, Keshav tries to poke inside the line and misses.
