Back of a length, around off. Tom Blundell keeps it out.
A length ball, around off. Conway blocks it off the front foot.
Mulder goes full around middle. Devon Conway covers the line of the ball and defends it.
Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Devon Conway works it to mid on.
A full ball, on middle. Devon Conway clips it to the leg side and takes a single.
On a length, outside off. Tom Blundell lets it be.
A full ball, outside off. Tom Blundell prods and leaves it alone.
On a good length, around off. Conway blocks it from the crease.
Length ball, on middle. Conway tucks it to square leg.
Slightly fuller around off, Conway presents the full face of his bat and drives it back at Rabada.
On a good length, outside off. Conway shoulders arms.
Full and outside off. Conway prods and watchfully blocks it out.
Sprays this one down the leg side. Conway goes for the pull but misses. Kyle Verreynne dives to his right and collects it. Half an appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire.
Fuller, on middle. Tom Blundell drives it to mid on.
Touch fuller, outside off. Tom Blundell taps it to the off side.
Short of a length, outside off. Blundell punches it to covers.
FOUR! Edgy! Length ball, around off. Tom Blundell prods and looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge past the gully fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, outside off. Tom Blundell stays solid in defence.
Starts with a loopy ball, full and on off. Conway presses forward to block.
Full and outside off, Conway reaches out and sweeps it to square leg.
FOUR! Nicely hit! Full again, outside off. Devon Conway reverse-sweeps it to deep point for a boundary.
Drags his length back, on off. Punched back to the bowler.
Tosses it up, outside off. Blocked out.
Flighted delivery, outside off. Swept again behind square on the leg side for a couple.
Short of a length, on off. Blundell punches it to the leg side.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Tom Blundell clips it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, outside off. Punched to wide of mid off for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Conway hops and taps it to point for a quick single.
On middle, kept out.
Full, on middle. Driven to mid on.
Flatter ball, outside off. Conway is solid in his defence.
Full and outside off, Conway defends it out.
Floats it up, outside off. Conway looks to sweep but adjusts and in the end, blocks it out.
Full and on middle. Conway reverse-sweeps it to deep point for a single.
Loopy ball, down the leg side. Left alone.
Short and on middle, Blundell defends it to short leg.
A length ball, on middle. Devon Conway dabs it with softs just in front of the short leg fielder.
A full ball, angling down leg. Conway misses his flick.
Short of a length, on middlel. Devon Conway keeps it out.
A length ball, around leg. Devon Conway flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full and outside off. Tom Blundell leans and drives it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Short of a length, on middle. Tom Blundell defends it to the on side.
FOUR! This is served down leg. Devon Conway kneels and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Around off, kept out.
Tosses it up, on off. Devon Conway reverse-sweeps it to deep point for a single.
On a length, around middle. Tom Blundell defends it out.
A loopy ball, on middle. Tom Blundell skips down the track and works it to mid-wicket.
Maharaj sees Tom Blundell advancing down the track so he serves a quicker ball, on middle. Tom Blundell dabs it onto the deck towards short leg.
A full ball, on middle. Devon Conway clips it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Full and outside off. Tom Blundell prods and pushes it to cover.
A full ball, well outside off. Tom Blundell lets it be.
FOUR! A rare full toss from Sipamla, around off. Tom Blundell drills it back past the bowler through mid off for a boundary.
This is full and wide, outside off. Tom Blundell leaves it alone.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Tom Blundell pushes it towards mid off.
Tossed up, on off. Devon Conway sweeps but straight towards the short fine leg fielder.
FOUR! Nicely done! Another ball, tossed up on middle. Devon Conway kneels and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.

NOT OUT! The extra bounce saves Conway! Maharaj tosses it up, on middle. Conway looks for a reverse-sweep but he misses and gets hit on his pad. Keshav Maharaj appeals but the umpire says no! Dean Elgar opts for a review but the Ball Tracker shows that the ball would have gone over the stumps.
Tossed up, on middle. Devon Conway sweeps it to backward square leg for a run.
Floated, down leg. Tom Blundell tucks it behind square on the leg side for a brace.
This is darted on the pads. Tom Blundell keeps it out.

OUT! LBW! Lutho Sipamla gets the big fish and South Africa get the much-needed breakthrough! A brilliant delivery from Sipamla and Conway didn't saw this coming! Sipamla serves a pinpoint yorker, around middle and leg. Conway fails to dig it out and gets hit low on his pad. Sipamla appeals and the umpire agrees. Conway opts for a review after consulting with his partner but the Ball Tracker shows three reds and Conway has to walk back. End of a gritty innings from the southpaw!
Howout: lbw b Lutho Sipamla

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme leaves it alone.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire says no! A length ball, jagging back in from middle. Colin de Grandhomme misses his flick and gets hit on his pad. Might have gone down leg.
On a length, around off. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme mistimes his drive towards the extra cover fielder.
FOUR! Finds the gap this time! A full ball, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme prods and carves it through the cover region for a boundary.
Flighted ball, on leg. Tom Blundell steps out and flicks it to short leg.
Slower through the air, on middle. Tom Blundell keeps it out.
Fired down leg, Tom Blundell tickles it to past leg slip for a couple of runs.
Short and on leg, punched to mid on.
Quicker delivery, on middle. Tom Blundell lunges forward and blocks it out.
Full and on the pads, Bundell stays solid in his defence.
FOUR! Lovely drive! Touch fuller from Sipamla, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme opens the full face of the bat and drives it past the bowler for a boundary.
On a good length, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme defends it out.
On the pads, whipped to deep square leg for a single.
On a good length, on off. Punched back to the bowler.
Full and angling in, on middle. Blundell prods and blocks it out.
Length ball, on off. Blundell defends it to silly mid on.
Quicker one, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme pats it back to the bowler.
Tosses it up nicely, on middle. CdG stays solid in his defence.
Full and on middle, kept out.
Floats it up, on the pads. Colin de Grandhomme defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery, on leg. Colin de Grandhomme clears his front leg and flicks it to mid-wicket.

Maiden over! Slower through the air, on middle and leg. Colin de Grandhomme gets low and goes for the sweep but misses. He gets thudded on the pads. An appeal for an lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Short of a length, on off. Tom Blundell gets behind the line and defends it out.
Short of a length again, on off. Tom Blundell blocks it right under his eyes.
An in-angler, on middle. Blundell clips it to square leg for a run.
Good-length ball, on top of off. Colin de Grandhomme stands tall and defends it back.
Back of a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme taps it to the off side.
Full and outside off. Colin de Grandhomme looks to drive but the ball goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on middle. Tom Blundell watchfully blocks it out.
Quicker one, on the pads. Colin de Grandhomme rocks back and knocks it back to Maharaj.
Floats it up, on leg. Kept out.
Short and on middle. blocked out.
On the pads, Colin de Grandhomme is solid in his defence.
A low full toss, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme prods and pushes it to long on for a single. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 5!
Jansen starts with a short ball, around leg. Colin de Grandhomme lets it sail through to the keeper.
Back of a length, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme keeps it out.
On a length, around middle. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it with ease.

An overthrow and they get one more! Good-length ball, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme nudges it behind square on the leg side for a single. The fielder there hurls a wayward throw at the striker's end and the batters take one more.
A short ball, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme pulls it along the ground towards fine leg for a single.
A full toss, outside off. Tom Blundell looks to drive but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.

DROPPED! Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Colin de Grandhomme looks to sweep but it goes off the top edge, in the air towards short fine leg. Rassie van der Dussen backtracks, misjudges it completely and puts it dwon. Keshav Maharaj can't believe it!
A quicker ball, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme punches it down to long on for a run.
Tossed up, around off. Tom Blundell keeps it out.
Floated, around middle. Tom Blundell presses forward to block.
A loopy ball, on middle. Tom Blundell skips down the track and works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, going on with the arm from middle. Tom Blundell hangs back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A bumper, down leg. Colin de Grandhomme sways away from the line of the ball.
A short ball, down leg. Colin de Grandhomme pulls it without much timing towards fine leg for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Marco Jansen strikes this time and more importantly, the catch has been taken! Another set batter departs and New Zealand are in deep trouble now! Marco Jansen persists with short-pitched stuff, on off. Tom Blundell is in two minds whether to play or leave. He does the former and miscues it in the air towards mid-wicket where Temba Bavuma takes a simple catch.
Howout: c Temba Bavuma b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Back of a length, on middle. Kyle Jamieson tucks it to the leg side.
A short ball, around middle. Kyle Jamieson looks to block off the back foot but it goes off the splice and lands safely in front of the mid-wicket fielder.
Another bumper, down leg. Kyle Jamieson ducks underneath.
Floated, on a length, around off. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.
Tosses it up, on off. Colin de Grandhomme skips down the track and eases it to long off for a single.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Kyle Jamieson pushes it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Tosses it up, on middle. Kyle Jamieson defends it.
Flatter ball, going on with the arm from off. Kyle Verreynne dabs it onto the deck.
An arm ball, around off. Kyle Jamieson stays back and blocks.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a terrific catch from Mulder at leg gully! A short ball, around leg. Colin de Grandhomme pulls it hard behind square on the leg side but hits it straight to Wiaan Mulder at leg gully who takes a sharp catch. New Zealand slip further!
Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Marco Jansen

Commentary: A well-directed bumper, on middle. Tim Southee looks to dab it down but it hits the splice of the bat and luckily for Southee, the ball pops out and flies just over the short leg fielder.
Back of a length, on middle. Tim Southee blocks it out.
Shorter in length, on off. Tim Southee blocks it out.
Back of a length, around off. Tim Southee hangs back and defends it.
Another shorter length delivery, around middle. Tim Southee hops in his crease and defends it with soft hands.
Floats it up, on leg. Kyle Jamieson clips it to square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, on leg. Tim Southee looks to play on th leg side but gets hit on the pads. Muted appeal for an lbw but it was goign down leg.
Full, on middle. Southee defends it out.
On the pads, nudged on the leg side.
Flatter ball, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
sliding on to the pads, Southee misses the tuck into the leg side.
Short of a length, on leg. Kyle Jamieson hops and works it to square leg for one.
Short ball again, on off. Tim Southee fends it away on the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Tim Southee blocks it out.
A bumper, on middle. Tim Southee sits under it.
And again! Another bouncer, on leg. Tim Southee sways away from the line and lets it go.
Short ball, on middle. Tim Southee negotiates with it nicely by blocking it on the leg side.
Tossed up, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, kept out.
FOUR! Up and over! Loopy ball, on leg. Kyle Jamieson advances down the track and lifts it over mid on for a boundary.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Kyle Jamieson works it off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on off. Defended back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, on off. Kyle stays solid in his defence.
Short of a length, on middle. Blocked out from the crease.
Short of a length again, on middle. Southee keeps blocking it out.
Back of a length yet again, on leg. Southee fends it away.
Bangs a bouncer, on middle. Southee ducks underneath.
Southee gets off the mark after facing 20 balls! Fuller in length, Southee drives it towards covers for a single.
This is tucked to fine leg by Jamieson for a single.
Loopy ball, on middle. Kyle Jamieson defends it out.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
On the pads, blocked out.
A yorker, on leg. Kyle Jamieson brings his bat down a little late. The ball rolls to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Tim Southee skips down and hits it back to the bowler.
Flatter one, angling in, Southee is hit on the pads but that was going down.

DROPPED! Oh dear! How did that go down? Jansen serves a short ball, on midde. Kyle Jamieson hangs back and looks to block. It hits the splice of his bat and pops out in front of him. Jansen goes for it and the fielder at silly point also looks to grab it. In the end, they both collide and none of them manage to gather the ball.
FOUR! A bumper, around off. Kyle Jamieson looks to heave it away but it goes off the top edge and flies over the slip cordon for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Kyle Jamieson holes out! Banged into the deck, on middle. Kyle Jamieson stands tall and looks to whack it over deep square leg. It goes off the top edge, in the air towards the deep square leg fielder where Kagiso Rabada takes a good catch running forward.
Howout: c Kagiso Rabada b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Short and going down leg, Tim Southee looks to pull but misses.
Back of a length, around off. Tim Southee keeps it out.
Another ball, shorter in length, on middle. Tim Southee defends it with soft hands.
Flatter ball, on off. Neil Wagner keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Neil Wagner hangs back to defend it.
BEATEN! Tosses it up, outside off. Neil Wagner looks for a booming drive but the ball beats his outside edge.
Slower through the air, outside off. Neil Wagner looks to push it through cover but it goes off the outside edge past the slip fielder and the batters take two runs.
Full and on middle. Neil Wagner keeps it out.
Floated, on a length, outside off. Neil Wagner looks to defend but he misses as the ball goes past his blade.
Back of a length, around off. Tim Southee dabs it onto the deck.
Shorter in length, around off. Tim Southee blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length, angling across the batter. Tim Southee lets it sail through to the keeper.
A short ball, around leg. Tim Southee pulls it behind square on the leg side and takes a single.
Jansen comes 'round the wicket and serves it on a length, around middle. Neil Wagner keeps it out.
Another ball, banged into the surface, around leg. Neil Wagner hops in his crease and dabs it to his right.
FOUR! Good use of the feet! Tossed up, on middle. Tim Southee skips down the track and lofts it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Slower through the air, on middle. Tim Southee rocks back to pull but it goes off the inside edge just past the leg stump.
Floated, full and outside off. Tim Southee chips it over the cover fielder and collects a couple of runs.
Tosses it up, around off. Tim Southee defends it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, on middle. Tim Southee skips down to slog but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Fuller in length, outside off. Tim Southee chips it just over the cover fielder and takes a couple of runs.
A short ball, around leg. Neil Wagner dabs it awkwardly behind square on the leg side for a run.
Shorter in length, on leg. Tim Southee swivels and tucks it towards the leg gully fielder.
Jansen goes full this time, outside off. Southee drags it back past the bowler towards long on for a couple of runs.
A short ball, on leg. Tim Southee nudges it behind square on the leg side and rotates the strike.

NOT OUT! Neil Wagner SURVIVES! Jansen serves another bouncer around middle. Neil Wagner tries to block it but he misses and there was some noise as the ball passed his bat. Marco Jansen appeals but the umpire says no! Dean Elgar opts for a review and the UlraEdge shows that there was no bat involved so the on-field decision remains.
Back of a length, outside off. Neil Wagner lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short ball, outside off. Tim Southee sits back and nicely ramps it to third man for a boundary.
Short of a length, on leg. Tim Southee looks to work it on the leg side but he misses. He gets hit on the thigh pad.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kagiso Rabada comes back into the attack and has done exactly what his skipper had asked. Bowls a short-of-a-length delivery, on leg. Tim Southee stays deep and miscues his heave. Gets a top edge and the ball lobs high in the air towards mid-wicket. Lutho Sipamla keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a fine catch. South Africa need just one wicket now to win this Test.
Howout: c Lutho Sipamla b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Fuller, on off. Wagner drives it through covers for a brace.
Bangs a bouncer, on leg. Neil Wagner sways away from the line and lets it go.
On a length, outside off. Neil Wagner pushes it to cover.
Short of a length, on middle. Henry keeps it out.
Sprays this one down leg, left alone.
Short ball, around off, the ball takes off after pitching. Matt Henry leaves it alone. Lovely leaping take by Verreynne.
Short and going down leg. Left alone.
A nasty bouncer, on middle. Matt Henry takes his eyes off the ball and somehow defends it out.
Another short ball, going down leg. Easy leave for Henry.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Length ball, outside off. Neil Wagner drives it uppishly, just over extra cover for a boundary.
On a good length, outside off. Kept out.
Short of a length, on middle. Neil Wagner blocks it out to the off side.
On a length, outside off. Wagner taps it to point.
Good-length ball, on off. Wagner blocks it out.
Good-length ball, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Short ball, on middle. Matt Henry sways away. He shows his back to the ball and takes a blow.
On a good length, on off. Henry pushes it to point.
Length ball, around off. Pushed to point.
On off, defended out.
Short of a length, on off. Matt Henry stands up on his toes and blocks it onto the deck.
A bouncer, on middle. Henry ducks under it.
Good-length ball, outside off. Wagner pushes it to cover.
On a length, on off. Wagner defends it to point.
Short ball, on off. Wagner hops and fends it away to the off side.

NOT OUT! Short ball, from 'round the wicket, on middle. Neil Wagner takes his eyes off the ball and lets it go with his bat hanging up. There was a noise heard and South Africa opt for a review as the umpire says no. But UltraEdge shows a flat line as the ball passes the bat. The original decision stands and South Africa don't have any reviews left.
Too short, on middle. Wagner leaves it alone.
Shortish again, outside off. Wagner punches it through covers for a single.
Short of a length again, outside off. Wagner dabs the ball to covers.
Wagner leaves this one alone as it is going down the leg side.
Absolute beauty! Bangs a bouncer, on middle. Neil Wagner drops his hands and gets hit on the shoulders.
On leg, Wagner misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Length ball, Wagner works it to short leg.
Shortish again, on leg. Wagner misses his flick and gets hit on the hips.
Full, on the pads. Pushed to mid on.
Full again, on leg. Once again, it is pushed to mid on.
Floats it up, on middle. Matt Henry defends it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Henry keeps it out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle. Defended out.
Short stuff continues! Short and on off, Wagner negotiates with it well.
Back of a lengh, on off. Wagner keeps it out.
Short of a length, outside off. Neil Wagner taps it to point.
Short ball, on middle. Wagner ducks underneath.
Back of a length, on off. Neil Wagner stays solid in his defence.
Fuller this time, outside off. Wagner pushes it towards covers.
Tossed up, on middle. Matt Henry lunges forward and blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on leg. Matt Henry pads it away. South Africa make a huge appeal for an lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Floats it up, on middle. Henry keeps it out.
Full and on middle, blocked out.

OUT! LBW! Keshav Maharaj ends the proceedings. Took a little longer than what they would have wanted but doesn't matter as they have won this Test. Flatter and quicker, on middle and leg, coming in with the angle. Matt Henry presses forward and looks to block but misses. He gets pinged on the front pad. Keshav Maharaj turns and appeals. The umpire raises his dreaded finger. Matt Henry does go for the review. The UltraEdge shows a flat line and the Ball Tracker shows all three reds. The on-field decision stands. Celebrations all around as South Africa win by 198 runs!
Howout: lbw b Keshav Maharaj
